acks%20electricity%2C%20water%2C%20food%2C%20medicines%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYesterday%20I%20had%2039%20babies%20and%20today%20they%20have%20become%2036%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Mohamed%20Tabasha%2C%20head%20of%20the%20paediatric%20department%20at%20Al%20Shifa%2C%20in%20a%20telephone%20interview%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20cannot%20say%20how%20long%20they%20can%20last.%20I%20can%20lose%20another%20two%20babies%20today%2C%20or%20in%20an%20hour%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20premature%20babies%2C%20who%20weigh%20less%20than%201.5%20kg%20(3.3%20pounds)%20each%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20only%20700%20or%20800%20grammes%2C%20should%20be%20in%20incubators%20where%20the%20temperature%20and%20humidity%20can%20be%20regulated%20according%20to%20their%20individual%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20they%20had%20to%20be%20moved%20to%20ordinary%20beds%20over%20the%20weekend%20because%20of%20a%20shortage%20of%20electricity%2C%20said%20Tabasha.%20They%20were%20placed%20side%20by%20side%2C%20surrounded%20by%20packets%20of%20nappies%2C%20cardboard%20boxes%20of%20sterile%20gauze%20and%20plastic%20bags.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20expected%20in%20my%20life%20that%20I%20would%20put%2039%20babies%20side%20by%20side%20on%20a%20bed%2C%20each%20with%20a%20different%20disease%2C%20and%20in%20this%20acute%20shortage%20of%20medical%20staff%2C%20of%20milk%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tabasha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20infants%20are%20too%20cold%2C%20and%20the%20temperature%20is%20not%20stable%20because%20of%20power%20cuts%2C%20he%20said.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20infection%20control%20measures%2C%20they%20are%20transmitting%20viruses%20to%20each%20other%20and%20they%20have%20no%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20there%20was%20no%20longer%20any%20way%20of%20sterilising%20their%20milk%20and%20bottle%20teats%20to%20the%20required%20standard.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20some%20had%20contracted%20gastritis%20and%20were%20suffering%20from%20diarrhoea%20and%20vomiting%2C%20which%20meant%20an%20acute%20risk%20of%20dehydration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'YOU%20SLOWLY%20KILL%20THEM'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Ahmed%20El%20Mokhallalati%2C%20also%20involved%20in%20caring%20for%20the%20babies%2C%20described%20the%20conditions%20as%20deadly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20in%20a%20very%20bad%20situation%20where%20you%20slowly%20kill%20them%20unless%20someone%20interferes%20to%20adjust%20or%20to%20improve%20their%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20also%20by%20telephone%20from%20Al%20Shifa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20very%20critical%20kinds%20of%20cases%2C%20where%20you%20have%20to%20be%20very%20sensitive%20in%20dealing%20with%20them.%20You%20have%20to%20take%20care%20of%20each%20of%20them%20in%20a%20very%20special%20way.%20Currently%20they%20are%20all%20in%20open%20space%2C%20they%20are%20all%20with%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETabasha%20listed%20everything%20he%20would%20need%20to%20keep%20the%20babies%20safe%3A%20electricity%20to%20run%20the%20incubators%2C%20a%20proper%20steriliser%20for%20the%20milk%20and%20bottle%20teats%2C%20medicines%2C%20and%20support%20machines%20in%20case%20any%20of%20them%20went%20into%20respiratory%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20situation%20was%20harrowing%20for%20the%20doctors%20and%20the%20four%20nurses%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20babies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20exhausted%20emotionally%20and%20physically%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20launched%20its%20military%20assault%20to%20destroy%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20group%20which%20runs%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20after%20Hamas%20fighters%20rampaged%20through%20southern%20Israel%20on%20Oct.%207%2C%20killing%20civilians.%20Around%201%2C200%20people%20died%20and%20240%20were%20taken%20hostage%2C%20according%20to%20Israel's%20tally%2C%20the%20deadliest%20day%