rsial%20perspective%20that%20calls%20for%20a%20serious%20and%20open%20discussion%20on%20animal%20ethics%20and%20sex%20ethics%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Princeton%20University%20bioethics%20professor%20added%2C%20encouraging%20people%20to%20%26quot%3Bread%20and%20ponder%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20promoting%20sex%20with%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESee%20the%20post%20here%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EAnother%20thought-provoking%20article%20is%20%26quot%3BZoophilia%20Is%20Morally%20Permissible%26quot%3B%20by%20Fira%20Bensto%20(pseudonym)%2C%20which%20is%20just%20out%20in%20the%20current%20issue%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJConIdeas%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40JConIdeas%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThis%20piece%20challenges%20one%20of%20society's%20strongest%20taboos%20and%20argues%20for%20the%20moral%20permissibility%20of%20some%20forms%20of%20sexual%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F32fIaJEJ1J%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F32fIaJEJ1J%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Peter%20Singer%20(%40PeterSinger)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPeterSinger%2Fstatus%2F1722440246972018857%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%209%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20journal%20says%20that%20animals%20can%20consent%20to%20sex%20with%20humans%20and%20it%20may%20not%20always%20be%20a%20harmful%20experience%20for%20them.%20The%20piece%20is%20available%20online.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20case%20for%20zoophilia%20being%20permissible%20is%20fairly%20robust%2C%20and%20commonly%20raised%20objections%20fall%20flat%20or%20are%20insufficiently%20backed%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20anonymous%20author%20wrote%20in%20the%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCritics%20of%20zoophilia%20need%20more%20than%20outrage%2C%20they%20need%20better%20arguments%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20concludes.%20%26quot%3BI%20suggest%20that%20the%20permissibility%20of%20zoophilia%20should%20now%20be%20taken%20as%20the%20default%20position%2C%20with%20the%20burden%20of%20proof%20belonging%20to%20its%20critics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Singer%20was%20slammed%20on%20social%20media%20for%20his%20thoughts.%20A%20user%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20nothing%20to%20ponder.%20People%20(almost%20always%20men)%20who%20rape%20and%20sexually%20molest%20animals%20should%20be%20in%20jail%20and%20on%20the%20sex%20offender%20register.%20Sex%20with%20someone%20who%20can't%20consent%20is%20rape.%20Next!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProfessor%2C%20Twitter%20is%20not%20a%20good%20venue%20for%20this.%20Earth%20also%20likely%20isn't%20a%20good%20a%20venue%2C%20but%20definitely%20not%20Twitter%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20user%20wrote%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRepent%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20third%20user%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Singer%20is%20best%20known%20for%20his%201975%20work%20%26quot%3BAnimal%20Liberation.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699878000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Ftmrqkka8_peter-singer_625x300_13_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-professor-stirs-controversy-for-encouraging-people-to-read-about-sex-with-animals-4570842%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Peter%20Singer%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Princeton%20University%20shared%20the%20study%2C%20asserting%20that%20the%20article%20challenges%20societal%20%26quot%3Btaboos%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-professor-stirs-controversy-for-encouraging-people-to-read-about-sex-with-animals-4570842%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-profes