e%20film.%20Despite%20whatever%20he%20might%20think%20of%20himself%2C%20he%20manages%20to%20find%20his%20moral%20centre%20to%20do%20the%20fair%20thing%2C%20even%20in%20the%20most%20unfair%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plot%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20painfully%20simple%3A%20A%20hitman%20botches%20up%20a%20job%2C%20and%20he%20goes%20on%20the%20run.%20Returning%20home%20to%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%2C%20he%20realises%20his%20employer%20has%20hurt%20his%20long-time%20partner%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20learn%20about%20his%20whereabouts.%20The%20protagonist%2C%20who%20never%20acts%20out%20of%20emotion%20%E2%80%93%20all%20his%20actions%20are%20measured%2C%20he%20blends%20into%20the%20crowd%20like%20sugar%20in%20hot%20milk%20%E2%80%93%20breaks%20his%20rules%20for%20love.%20He%20seeks%20out%20his%20handler%20Hodges%20%5BCharles%20Parnell%5D%2C%20the%20assassins%20sent%20to%20torture%20his%20partner%2C%20and%20the%20client%20%E2%80%93%20a%20billionaire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20plot%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20seems%20direct%2C%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20far-fetched%20to%20think%20that%20the%20film%20could%20present%20itself%20as%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20director%E2%80%99s%20tempestuous%20relationship%20with%20the%20studios%20over%20his%20three-decade%20career.%20Just%20look%20out%20for%20the%20caption%20on%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20poster%3A%20execution%20is%20everything.%20Those%20are%20words%20for%20a%20filmmaker%20to%20die%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFincher%E2%80%99s%20run-ins%20with%20the%20Hollywood%20system%20have%20been%20the%20stuff%20of%20legends%2C%20especially%20the%20way%20he%20began%20his%20career%20with%20the%20troubled%20production%20of%20%3Cem%3EAlien%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1992).%20After%20his%20adaptation%20of%20Steig%20Larsson%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EMillennium%3C%2Fem%3E%20trilogy%20was%20shut%20down%20following%20just%20one%20film%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Girl%20with%20The%20Dragon%20Tattoo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%2C%20and%20the%20show%20%3Cem%3EMindhunter%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2017-2019)%20was%20discontinued%20after%20two%20seasons%20for%20being%20%E2%80%98too%20expensive%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20numbers%20it%20ended%20up%20drawing%2C%20one%20can%20almost%20sense%20the%20weariness%20in%20the%2061-year-old%20filmmaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20previous%20film%2C%20%3Cem%3EMank%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2021)%2C%20a%20black-and-white%2C%20no-questions-asked%20passion%20project%2C%20based%20on%20a%20screenplay%20written%20by%20his%20father%20(Jack%20Fincher)%20on%20the%20making%20of%20%3Cem%3ECitizen%20Kane%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1931)%2C%20felt%20like%20one%20of%20his%20more%20personal%20films.%20And%20now%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eit%20feels%20like%20Fincher%20is%20looking%20inwards%20more%20than%20outwards%20for%20inspiration.%20Even%20his%20choice%20of%20actor%2C%20Michael%20Fassbender%2C%20who%20was%20brought%20out%20of%20hibernation%20after%20being%20chewed%20out%20in%20six%20consecutive%20studio%20flops%2C%20seems%20to%20be%20telling%20its%20own%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdapted%20from%20a%20French%20graphic%20novel%20of%20the%20same%20name%20by%20Alexis%20%E2%80%98Matz%E2%80%99%20Nolent%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20opens%20with%20the%20protagonist%20talking%20about%20how%20contract%20killing%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20job%20worth%20pursuing%20if%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20endure%20the%20waiting.%20He%20could%20be%20talking%20about%20filmmaking%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20a%20vocation%20about%20which%20actor%20John%20Candy%20once%20remarked%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20get%20paid%20for%20waiting%2C%20I%20throw%20in%20the%20acting%20for%20free!%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20Fincher%20at%20his%20most%20indulgent%20%E2%80%93%20sharing%20his%20philosophies%20with%20the%20world%20through%20a%20protagonist%20who%20is%20as%20dry%2C%20disciplined%2C%20meticulous%20and%20proud%20as%20a%20craftsman%20as%20the%20filmmaker%20is.%20Over%20the%20normal%20course%20of%20events%2C%20the%20protagonist%20dispassionately%20looks%20at%20life%20as%20something%20to%20endure.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20self-centered%20way%20of%20living%20saying%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20give%20a%20damn%E2%80%9D%20about%20anything%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20help%20him%20in%20his%20work.%20That%E2%80%99s%20until%20someone%20hurts%20a%20loved%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFincher%20takes%20the%20template%20of%20hitman%20films%20like%20%3Cem%3EJason%20Bourne%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3EJohn%20Wick%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20slowly%20draining%20all%20the%20sexiness%20out%20of%20it.%20It%20seems%20a%20very%20deliberate%20choice%2C%20where%20he%20takes%20the%20very%20template%20of%20a%20genre%20he%20has%20helped%20establish%2C%20and%20turns%20it%20inside%20out.%20Fassbender%20%E2%80%93%20who%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20starred%20in%20movies%20in%20three%20years%20%E2%80%93%20seems%20to%20be%20enjoying%20his%20director%E2%80%99s%20quiet%20rebellion%20against%20what%20is%20expected%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98cool%E2%80%99%20Fincher%20film.%20He%E2%80%99s%20dressed%20and%20styled%20unmemorably%20throughout%2C%20in%20Khakis%2C%20tracksuits%2C%20baseball%20caps.%20Even%20though%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20usual%20globetrotting%20in%20a%20film%20like%20this%2C%20where%20the%20killer%20hops%20on%20transcontinental%20flights%20like%20they%20were%20local%20trains%20in%20Bombay%2C%20Fincher%20never%20milks%20the%20changing%20geography%20with%20the%20cliched%20top-shot%20of%20a%20city%2C%20with%20the%20name%20appearing%20as%20a%20title%20card%20on%20screen.%20Instead%2C%20he%20makes%20mundane%20observations%20about%20them%20like%20any%20world-weary%20traveller%3A%20%E2%80%9CParis%20is%20a%20city%20that%20wakes%20up%20slowly%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CNew%20Orleans%2C%20a%20thousand%20restaurants%E2%80%A6%20one%20menu.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20one%20fist%20fight%20sequence%20in%20the%20entire%20film%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%20seems%20to%20be%20designed%20in%20a%20way%20to%20look%20functional%2C%20not%20stylish.%20However%2C%20Fincher%E2%80%99s%20precision%20shows%20up%20in%20the%20closing%20moments%20of%20the%20scene%2C%20when%20the%20killer%20needs%20to%20escape%20a%20pitbull.%20The%20timing%20and%20choreography%20of%20this%20last%20bit%20is%20unsurprisingly%20exquisite.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20scene%20featuring%20%E2%80%98The%20Expert%E2%80%99%20(Tilda%20Swinton)%2C%20where%20Fincher%20clasps%20the%20breaks%20on%20the%20film%2C%20allowing%20someone%20other%20than%20his%20protagonist%20to%20ruminate%20on%20their%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20do%20we%20do%20the%20things%20we%20do%3F%20Even%20while%20paying%20the%20price%20of%20our%20mental%20well-being%2C%20battling%20unfavourable%20situations%2C%20choosing%20our%20calling%20over%20an%20impersonal%20job%20that%20will%20help%20us%20lead%20a%20sane%2C%20bloodless%2C%20probably%20boring%20life%3F%20Are%20we%20all%20masochists%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20sequence%20worthy%20of%20Tilda%20Swinton%E2%80%99s%20starry%20presence%2C%20when%20she%20makes%20her%20moves%20with%20words%20and%20glances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20might%20suggest%20that%20Fincher%20is%20grappling%20with%20his%20own%20label%20as%20a%20cold%2C%20clinical%20genius%2C%20who%20prioritises%20perfection%20over%20vulnerability%2C%20precision%20over%20humanity.%20However%2C%20as%20the%20climax%20of%20the%20film%20suggests%2C%20he%20wants%20to%20continue%20doing%20what%20he%20loves%2C%20even%20as%20his%20disdain%20for%20having%20to%20fight%20for%20his%20terms%20might%20be%20starting%20to%20take%20a%20toll%20on%20him.%20Unlike%20what%20many%20of%20his%20fans%20think%2C%20Fincher%20sees%20himself%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeep%20down%20somewhere%2C%20despite%20what%20he%20has%20said%20in%20the%20past%2C%20David%20Fincher%20still%20gives%20a%20f%23%24k.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699875042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13161217%2Fimage-1495.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-killer-the-clinical-assassin-in-a-film-made-by-a-clinical-director-david-fincher%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20film%20reflects%20the%20disdain%20the%20director%20has%20felt%20over%20the%20years%20for%20Hollywood%20studios%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-killer-the-clinical-assassin-in-a-film-made-by-a-clinical-director-david-fincher%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20India%20Is%20Shifting%20Its%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plans%20Into%20High%20Gear%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F03162440%2Fimage-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2014%20last%20year%2C%20Union%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20Atomic%20Energy%20and%20Space%20Jitendra%20Singh%20made%20an%20announcement%20with%20far-reaching%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20written%20reply%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Singh%20said%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20NDA%20government%20will%20commission%2020%20new%20nuclear%20reactors%20by%202031.%20With%20that%2C%20he%20said%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20installed%20nuclear%20capacity%20will%20treble%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2F20-new-nuclear-plants-to-be-commissioned-in-country-by-2031-minister-in-lok-sabha%2Farticleshow%2F96232288.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrent%207%2C480%20megawatt%20(MW)%20to%2022%2C480%20MW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETen%20of%20these%20reactors%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20500%20MW%20Prototype%20Fast%20Breeder%20Reactor%20at%20Kalpakkam%20and%20the%20two%201%2C000%20MW%20reactors%20at%20Kudankulam%20%E2%80%93%20are%20already%20under%20construction.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20government%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2F20-new-nuclear-plants-to-be-commissioned-in-country-by-2031-minister-in-lok-sabha%2Farticleshow%2F96232288.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egranted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cadministrative%20and%20financial%20sanctions%E2%80%9D%20for%20building%2010%20more%20nuclear%20plants%20with%20700%20MW%20Pressurised%20Heavy%20Water%20Reactors%20at%20Gorakhpur%20(Haryana)%2C%20Kaiga%20(Karnataka)%2C%20Chutka%20(Madhya%20Pradesh)%20and%20Mahi%20Banswara%20(Rajasthan).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20just%20the%20start.%20Another%20clutch%20of%20reactors%20have%20secured%20in-principle%20approvals.%20Once%20all%20these%20projects%20are%20up%2C%20the%20number%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20reactors%20will%20rise%20from%20the%20current%2022%20to%20well%20above%2050.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20not%20all.%20The%20NDA%20government%20is%20also%20bullish%20on%20SMRs%2C%20typically%20below%20300%20MW%20in%20capacity%2C%20and%20wants%20to%20use%20them%20for%20both%20power%20generation%20and%20to%20decarbonise%20industry.%20National%20Thermal%20Power%20Corporation%20(NTPC)%20is%20thinking%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fcompanies%2Fpower-giant-ntpc-to-build-nuclear-fleet-to-aid-climate-goal-chase%2Farticle66238287.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretro-fitting%20small%20modular%20reactors%20(SMRs)%20into%20decommissioned%20coal%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20August%2C%20speaking%20at%20a%20conclave%20on%20green%20hydrogen%20and%20net%20zero%2C%20senior%20NITI%20Aayog%20official%20V.K.%20Saraswat%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Feducation%2Fnews%2Fadvancing-indias-net-zero-mission-conclave-explores-green-hydrogen-production%2Farticleshow%2F102712272.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindustrial%20units%20too%20should%20use%20SMRs%20to%20produce%20hydrogen%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20projected%20numbers%20are%20mind-boggling.%20The%20installed%20capacity%20of%20coal-fired%20plants%20in%20India%20stands%20around%20220%20gigawatt%20(GW).%20%E2%80%9C%5BOf%20this%20220%20GW%5D%2C%2020%20GW%20is%20already%20off%20the%20grid%20and%20gradually%20others%20will%20also%20be%20coming%20in%20the%20line%2C%E2%80%9D%20A.K.%20Nayak%2C%20head%20(Nuclear%20Control%20and%20Program%20Wing)%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Atomic%20Energy%20said%20last%20December%20at%20a%20conference%20organised%20by%20India%20Nuclear%20Business%20Platform%2C%20a%20nuclear%20power%20advocacy%20firm%20owned%20by%20a%20Singapore-based%20consultancy%20called%20Industry%20Platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%2C%20he%20said%2C%20can%20be%20refitted%20with%20SMRs.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20big%20opportunity%20for%20SMRs%20in%20a%20span%20of%202-3%20decades%E2%80%A6%20For%20interested%20companies%20like%20NTPC%20and%20others%20it%20is%20a%20business%20opportunity%20of%20220%20GW.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20such%20projections%2C%20SMRs%20might%20play%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20India%20than%20large%20reactors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_4badb5-27%5C%22%3ET%3Cstrong%3Ehe%20case%20for%20nuclear%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20curious%20silence%20has%20accompanied%20most%20of%20these%20plans.%20Barring%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-india-plans-to-use-nuclear-power-to-achieve-net-zero-emissions-international-atomic-energy-agency-vienna-4430090%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eodd%20media%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0outlining%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20plans%20for%20nuclear%20power%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fmultimedia%2Fvideo%2Fwhy-small-modular-reactors-are-key-to-indias-decarbonisation-goals%2Farticle67187868.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eop-eds%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Fnuclear-power-space-india-strategic-sectors-private-8930052%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efavour%20of%20SMRs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20has%20not%20been%20enough%20critical%20discussion%20around%20this%20proposed%20nuclear%20buildup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20nuclear%20energy%20help%20India%20step%20away%20from%20coal%3F%20Has%20the%20industry%20resolved%20its%20old%20problems%20with%20cost-%20and%20time-overruns%3F%20What%20about%20public%20safety%3F%20Given%20the%20world%20continues%20to%20innovate%20in%20renewables%2C%20should%20India%20go%20for%20100%25%20renewables%20or%20push%20to%20add%20nuclear%20capacity%20as%20well%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20energy%20front%2C%20the%20country%20is%20stuck%20between%20a%20rock%20and%20a%20hard%20place.%20In%202022-23%2C%20its%20power%20demand%20stood%20at%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Fpower-consumption-grows-9-5-pc-to-1503-billion-units-in-2022-23-govt-data%2Farticleshow%2F99530203.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%2C503%20billion%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20(BUs).%20This%20demand%20was%20met%20through%20an%20installed%20power%20generation%20capacity%20of%20415.4%20GW%2C%20with%20236.68%20GW%20coming%20from%20coal%2C%20lignite%20and%20gas.%20Renewables%20%E2%80%93%20hydel%2C%20solar%2C%20bio-energy%2C%20wind%20and%20pumped%20storage%20%E2%80%93%20accounted%20for%20171.8%20GW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20India%20decarbonises%2C%20not%20only%20will%20most%20of%20these%20thermal%20units%20be%20wound%20down%2C%20the%20country%20will%20also%20see%20additional%20demand%20for%20electricity%20as%20other%20users%20of%20hydrocarbons%20%E2%80%93%20like%20factories%20and%20vehicles%20%E2%80%93%20electrify%20as%20well.%20By%202030%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Electricity%20Authority%20expects%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20electricity%20demand%20to%20touch%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcea.nic.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Firp%2F2023%2F05%2FOptimal_mix_report__2029_30_Version_2.0__For_Uploading.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2%2C279%20BU%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%202050%2C%20says%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energymonitor.ai%2Fpolicy%2Fhow-india-could-reach-net-zero-by-2050%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnergy%20Monitor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20power%20demand%20might%20touch%205%2C921%20BUs.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20the%20country%20might%20need%20as%20much%20as%204%2C000%20GW%20of%20installed%20capacity%20%E2%80%93%20almost%20a%2010-fold%20jump%20from%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20where%20a%20massive%20constraint%20asserts%20itself.%20India%E2%80%99s%20potential%20RE%20capacity%20%E2%80%93%20between%20hydel%2C%20solar%20and%20wind%20%E2%80%93%20is%20currently%20estimated%20at%20no%20more%20than%201%2C000%20GW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20gets%20worse.%20The%20country%20cannot%20build%20to%20full%20potential%20capacity%20%E2%80%93%20building%20145%2C000%20MW%20of%20dams%20will%20extract%20its%20own%20social%20and%20ecological%20costs.%20As%20will%20unfettered%20expansion%20of%20solar%20parks%20and%20wind%20farms.%20India%20can%20reduce%20total%20future%20power%20demand%20%E2%80%93%20by%20slashing%20transmission%20and%20distribution%20losses%20or%20by%20providing%20Indians%20lower%20per%20capita%20power%20than%20the%20global%20average%20by%20embracing%20greater%20energy%20efficiency%20%E2%80%93%20but%20there%20will%20still%20be%20a%20shortfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20morning%20in%20April%2C%20seeking%20to%20understand%20all%20this%20better%2C%20%3Cem%3ECarbonCopy%3C%2Fem%3E%20met%20nuclear%20scientist%20Ravi%20Grover%20at%20his%20office%20in%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s%20Bhabha%20Atomic%20Research%20Centre.%20Given%20the%20size%20of%20its%20population%2C%20he%20said%20in%20that%20chat%2C%20India%20will%20have%20to%20use%20all%20the%20energy%20options%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20morning%2C%20Grover%20outlined%20another%20reason%20why%20India%20needs%20nuclear%20power.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20power%20supply%20was%20constant%20(thanks%20to%20thermal%20power%20plants)%20while%20demand%20waxed%20and%20waned.%20%E2%80%9CBalance%20between%20supply%20and%20demand%20was%20usually%20maintained%20through%20load-shedding%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3ECarbonCopy%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20changing%20now%2C%20he%20said.%20As%20the%20share%20of%20renewables%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20energy%20mix%20rises%2C%20both%20supply%20and%20demand%20will%20become%20variable.%20The%20country%E2%80%99s%20electricity%20system%20will%20need%20additional%20investments%20%E2%80%93%20pumped%20storage%2C%20battery%20storage%2C%20electrolysers%2C%20what%20have%20you%20%E2%80%93%20to%20balance%20demand%20and%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelivering%20what%20Grover%20describes%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.currentscience.ac.in%2FVolumes%2F123%2F11%2F1309.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECurrent%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0as%20%E2%80%9Cfirm%20power%E2%80%9D%2C%20nuclear%20power%20can%20also%20help%20address%20intermittency.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20India%20wants%20200%20GW%20of%20renewable%20power%2C%20then%20we%20should%20try%20to%20have%2020-40%20GW%20of%20nuclear%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3ECarbonCopy.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20what%20the%20world%20is%20doing.%20The%20UK%20will%20be%2025%25%20nuclear%20by%20the%20middle%20of%20this%20century.%20France%20is%20adding%20eight%20to%2014%20new%20reactors.%20India%2C%20too%2C%20needs%20to%20add%20three%20to%20four%20times%20as%20much%20nuclear%20capacity.%20What%20we%20have%20is%20not%20enough.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20however%2C%20one%20big%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_36307d-6c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBroken%20promises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20India%20has%20mapped%20out%20a%20large%20buildup%20of%20nuclear%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20too%2C%20variably%20citing%20military%20security%2C%20energy%20security%20and%20looming%20energy%20shortages%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20establishment%20has%20pushed%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Framana%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erapid%20expansion%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20power%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201954%2C%20Homi%20Bhabha%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20programme%2C%20said%20India%20would%20have%208%2C000%20MW%20of%20nuclear%20capacity%20by%201980.%20In%201960%2C%20the%20country%20was%20told%20it%20would%20have%2043%2C500%20MW%20by%202000.%20In%201984%2C%20a%20decade%20after%20the%201974%20nuclear%20test%2C%20the%20country%20was%20promised%2010%2C000%20MW%20by%202000.%20The%20actual%20installed%20capacity%20was%20about%20600%20MW%20in%201980%20and%202%2C720%20MW%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201999%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20establishment%20said%20the%20country%20would%20have%2020%2C000%20MW%20by%202020.%20In%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20the%20DAE%20(Department%20of%20Atomic%20Energy)%20upped%20that%20target%20to%20275%20GW%20by%202052%20%E2%80%93%20and%20then%20to%20470%20GW%20after%20the%20US-India%20nuclear%20deal.%20India%20missed%20those%20targets%20as%20well.%20Today%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20installed%20nuclear%20capacity%20stands%20at%207%2C480%20MW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20clutch%20of%20factors%20are%20responsible%20for%20this%20under-delivery.%20Some%20are%20global.%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20tests%20left%20the%20country%20struggling%20to%20source%20technology%20and%20nuclear%20fuels.%20In%20more%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20Nuclear%20Liability%20Act%20has%20dissuaded%20foreign%20nuclear%20suppliers%20from%20entering%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20are%20local.%20As%20physicist%20M.V.%20Ramana%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpenguin.co.in%2Fbook%2Fthe-power-of-promise%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Power%20of%20Promise%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20his%202012%20book%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20power%20aspirations%2C%20lack%20of%20scale%20has%20been%20a%20problem.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20problem%20was%20not%20that%20the%20industry%20lacked%20the%20technological%20base%20needed%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20fabrication%20%5Bof%20the%20reactors%5D%2C%20but%20that%20the%20few%20orders%20that%20it%20received%20from%20the%20DAE%20did%20not%20make%20it%20economical%20for%20companies%20to%20do%20so.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELand%20acquisition%20has%20been%20another%20bugbear.%20Design%20changes%20during%20construction%20are%20yet%20another.%20In%20all%2C%20as%20Ramana%20wrote%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20plants%20have%20been%20plagued%20by%20cost-%20and%20time-overruns%2C%20and%20performed%20worse%20than%20envisaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20things%20get%20interesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_44012e-94%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStepping%20around%20past%20glitches%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20the%20latest%20nuclear%20buildup%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20meet%20the%20fate%20of%20its%20predecessors%2C%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20government%20has%20made%20two%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20Nuclear%20Power%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(NPCIL)%20has%20been%20told%20to%20jointly%20develop%20nuclear%20plants%20with%20firms%20like%20NTPC.%20The%20rationale%3F%20Not%20only%20can%20NTPC%20raise%20funds%20more%20easily%20than%20NPCIL%2C%20by%20pooling%20their%20strengths%20in%20project%20management%20and%20nuclear%20plant%20design%2C%20NPCIL%20and%20NTPC%20can%20set%20up%20nuclear%20plants%20faster.%20This%20point%20was%20made%20at%20the%20India%20Nuclear%20Business%20Platform%20conference%20last%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%20NPCIL%20was%20executing%20one%20or%20two%20projects%20at%20a%20time%2C%20but%20now%20with%20capacity%20getting%20ramped%20up%20substantially%2C%20the%20plan%20is%20that%20NPCIL%20along%20with%20NTPC%20will%20be%20running%20at%20least%2010%20nuclear%20projects%20at%20a%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20R.%20Sharan%2C%20director%20(projects)%2C%20NPCIL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20seeking%20to%20obviate%20risks%20like%20time%2Fcost%20overruns%20and%20the%20difficulty%20of%20land%20acquisition%2C%20the%20NDA%20is%20bullish%20on%20SMRs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tandem%2C%20it%20is%20also%20getting%20easier%20for%20India%20to%20source%20nuclear%20technology%20from%20outside.%20As%20nuclear%20energy%20tries%20to%20regain%20ground%20lost%20to%20renewables%2C%20a%20bevy%20of%20large%20reactor%20makers%20and%20SMR%20manufacturers%20are%20competing%20to%20crack%20markets%20like%20India.%20Anyone%20trying%20to%20understand%20the%20role%20of%20nuclear%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20emerging%20energy%20mix%20has%20to%20engage%20with%20these%20shifts%20in%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20questions%2C%20therefore%2C%20arise.%20Both%20the%20NPCIL-NTPC%20alliance%20and%20SMRs%20are%20untested%20experiments.%20Can%20they%20deliver%3F%20Further%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fjoule%2Ffulltext%2FS2542-4351(23)00281-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20competitive%20landscape%20for%20nuclear%20power%20is%20changing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20no%20longer%20competes%20with%20coal%20and%20gas.%20Instead%2C%20billions%20are%20being%20spent%20to%20boost%20efficiency%20of%20existing%20renewable%20technologies%20like%20solar%20panels%2C%20wind%20turbines%2C%20rechargeable%20batteries%20and%20develop%20newer%20sources%20of%20renewable%20power%20like%20electrolysers.%20Countries%20are%20also%20experimenting%20with%20technologies%20like%20pumped%20storage%20and%20grid%20management%20to%20create%20100%25%20renewable%20grids.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20can%20SMRs%E2%80%94and%20NTPC%E2%80%94carve%20out%20a%20perch%20for%20nuclear%20power%20in%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20part%20of%20the%20series%20will%20look%20into%20this%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2Fhow-india-is-shifting-its-nuclear-power-plans-into-high-gear%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2F%5C%22%3ECarbon%20Copy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699874152000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F03162440%2Fimage-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fhow-india-is-shifting-its-nuclear-power-plans-into-high-gear%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20country%20needs%20to%20decarbonise.%20Its%20renewables%20face%20charges%20of%20intermittency.%20Is%20nuclear%20the%20answer%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fhow-india-is-shifting-its-nuclear-power-plans-into-high-gear%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IT%20services%20companies%20chase%20large%20deals%20for%20higher%20revenue%2C%20faster%20growth%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699874028000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2020-01%2F05%2Ffull%2F1578243325-0995.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fit-services-companies-chase-large-deals-for-higher-revenue-faster-growth-123111300660_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22IT%20companies%20consider%20deals%20at%20or%20above%20%24100%20million%20as%20large%20deals%20while%20deals%20at%20or%20above%20%24500%20million%20are%20categorised%20as%20mega%20deals%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fit-services-companies-chase-large-deals-for-higher-revenue-faster-growth-123111300660_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fit-services-companies-chase-large-deals-for-higher-revenue-faster-growth-123111300660_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fit-services-companies-chase-large-deals-for-higher-revenue-faster-growth-123111300660_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trade%20Unions%20Denounce%20Israeli%20Call%20to%20Replace%20Palestinian%20Workers%2C%20Urge%20India%20to%20Reject%20Request%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13152108%2Fimage-1494.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20a%20strongly%20worded%20joint%20statement%20issued%20on%20November%209%2C%20ten%20major%20trade%20unions%20in%20India%2C%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20the%20Joint%20Platform%20of%20Central%20Trade%20Unions%20and%20Independent%20Federations%2C%20called%20on%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20reject%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20construction%20sector%E2%80%99s%20request%20to%20replace%20Palestinian%20workers%20with%20Indian%20workers%20amid%20the%20ongoing%20war%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fjaishankar-hama