023%2F11%2F09170130%2Fsj-objio-8hHxO3iYuU0-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20much%20about%20being%20able%20to%20access%20a%20course%20of%20antibiotics%20to%20head%20off%20an%20infection.%20But%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20always%20the%20case%20%E2%80%93%20antibiotics%20have%20been%20available%20for%20less%20than%20a%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%2C%20patients%20would%20die%20of%20relatively%20trivial%20infections%20that%20became%20more%20serious.%20Some%20serious%20infections%2C%20such%20as%20those%20involving%20the%20heart%20valves%2C%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F20173297%2F%5C%22%3Einevitably%3C%2Fa%3E%20fatal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20serious%20infections%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3070694%2F%5C%22%3Etuberculosis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20weren%E2%80%99t%20always%20fatal.%20Up%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.biorxiv.org%2Fcontent%2F10.1101%2F729426v1.full.pdf%5C%22%3Ehalf%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20people%20died%20within%20a%20year%20with%20the%20most%20severe%20forms%2C%20but%20some%20people%20recovered%20without%20treatment%20and%20the%20remainder%20had%20ongoing%20chronic%20infection%20that%20slowly%20ate%20away%20at%20the%20body%20over%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20had%20antibiotics%2C%20the%20outcomes%20for%20these%20infections%20were%20much%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20(and%20death)%20before%20antibiotics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%E2%80%99ve%20probably%20heard%20of%20Alexander%20Fleming%E2%80%99s%20accidental%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acs.org%2Feducation%2Fwhatischemistry%2Flandmarks%2Fflemingpenicillin.html%5C%22%3Ediscovery%20of%20penicillin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20fungal%20spores%20landed%20on%20a%20plate%20with%20bacteria%20left%20over%20a%20long%20weekend%20in%201928.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ox.ac.uk%2Fnews%2Fscience-blog%2Fpenicillin-oxford-story%5C%22%3Efirst%20patient%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20receive%20penicillin%20was%20an%20instructive%20example%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20treatment.%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%201941%2C%20Constable%20Albert%20Alexander%20had%20a%20scratch%20on%20his%20face%20that%20had%20become%20infected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20hospitalised%20but%20despite%20various%20treatments%2C%20the%20infection%20progressed%20to%20involve%20his%20head.%20This%20required%20removing%20one%20of%20his%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684313%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIn%201941%2C%20Albert%20Alexander%20was%20hospitalised%20with%20a%20severe%20infection.%20Photo%3A%20Jonathan%20Borba%2FPexels%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHoward%20Florey%2C%20the%20Australian%20pharmacologist%20then%20working%20in%20Oxford%2C%20was%20concerned%20penicillin%20could%20be%20toxic%20in%20humans.%20Therefore%2C%20he%20felt%20it%20was%20only%20ethical%20to%20give%20this%20new%20drug%20to%20a%20patient%20in%20a%20desperate%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConstable%20Alexander%20was%20given%20the%20available%20dose%20of%20penicillin.%20Within%20the%20first%20day%2C%20his%20condition%20had%20started%20to%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20back%20then%2C%20penicillin%20was%20difficult%20to%20produce.%20One%20way%20of%20extending%20the%20limited%20supply%20was%20to%20%E2%80%9Crecycle%E2%80%9D%20penicillin%20that%20was%20excreted%20in%20the%20patient%E2%80%99s%20urine.%20Despite%20this%2C%20supplies%20ran%20out%20by%20the%20fifth%20day%20of%20Alexander%E2%80%99s%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20further%20treatment%2C%20the%20infection%20again%20took%20hold.%20Constable%20Alexander%20eventually%20died%20a%20month%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20now%20face%20a%20world%20where%20we%20are%20potentially%20running%20out%20of%20antibiotics%20%E2%80%93%20not%20because%20of%20difficulties%20manufacturing%20them%2C%20but%20because%20they%E2%80%99re%20losing%20their%20effectiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20we%20use%20antibiotics%20for%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20currently%20use%20antibiotics%20in%20humans%20and%20animals%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons.%20Antibiotics%20reduce%20the%20duration%20of%20illness%20and%20the%20chance%20of%20death%20from%20infection.%20They%20also%20prevent%20infections%20in%20people%20who%20are%20at%20high%20risk%2C%20such%20as%20patients%20undergoing%20surgery%20and%20those%20with%20weakened%20immune%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20antibiotics%20aren%E2%80%99t%20always%20used%20appropriately.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flaninf%2Farticle%2FPIIS1473-3099(20)30084-0%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3EStudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20consistently%20show%20a%20dose%20or%20two%20will%20adequately%20prevent%20infections%20after%20surgery%2C%20but%20antibiotics%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firp.cdn-website.com%2Fd820f98f%2Ffiles%2Fuploaded%2Fsurgical-prophylaxis-prescribing-in-australian-hospitals-results-of-the-2020-surgical-national-antimicrobial-prescribing-survey.pdf%5C%22%3Eoften%3C%2Fa%3E%20continued%20for%20several%20days%20unnecessarily.%20And%20sometimes%20we%20use%20the%20wrong%20type%20of%20antibiotic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firp.cdn-website.com%2Fd820f98f%2Ffiles%2Fuploaded%2Fantimicrobial-prescribing-practice-in-australian-hospitals-results-of-the-2020-hospital-national-antimicrobial-prescribing-survey.pdf%5C%22%3ESurveys%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%2022%25%20of%20antimicrobial%20use%20in%20hospitals%20is%20inappropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684314%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAntibiotics%20are%20used%20for%20longer%20than%20needed%20and%20sometimes%20the%20wrong%20type%20is%20used.%20Photo%3A%20National%20Cancer%20Institute%2FUnsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20situations%2C%20this%20is%20understandable.%20Infections%20in%20different%20body%20sites%20are%20usually%20due%20to%20different%20types%20of%20bacteria.%20When%20the%20diagnosis%20isn%E2%80%99t%20certain%2C%20we%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fresp.13334%5C%22%3Eerr%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20side%20of%20caution%20by%20giving%20broad%20spectrum%20antibiotics%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20have%20active%20treatments%20for%20all%20possible%20infections%2C%20until%20further%20information%20becomes%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20situations%2C%20there%20is%20a%20degree%20of%20inertia.%20If%20the%20patient%20is%20improving%2C%20doctors%20tend%20to%20simply%20continue%20the%20same%20treatment%2C%20rather%20than%20change%20to%20more%20appropriate%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20general%20practice%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20diagnostic%20uncertainty%20and%20therapeutic%20inertia%20are%20often%20magnified.%20Patients%20who%20recover%20after%20starting%20antibiotics%20don%E2%80%99t%20usually%20require%20tests%20or%20come%20back%20for%20review%2C%20so%20there%20is%20no%20easy%20way%20of%20knowing%20if%20the%20antibiotic%20was%20actually%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotic%20prescribing%20can%20be%20more%20complex%20again%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mja.com.au%2Fjournal%2F2014%2F201%2F2%2Fantibiotic-prescribing-practice-residential-aged-care-facilities-health-care%5C%22%3Epatients%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20expecting%20%E2%80%9Ca%20pill%20for%20every%20ill%E2%80%9D.%20While%20doctors%20are%20generally%20good%20at%20educating%20patients%20when%20antibiotics%20are%20not%20likely%20to%20work%20(for%20example%2C%20for%20viral%20infections)%2C%20without%20confirmatory%20tests%20there%20can%20always%20be%20a%20lingering%20doubt%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20both%20doctors%20and%20patients.%20Or%20sometimes%20the%20patient%20goes%20elsewhere%20to%20find%20a%20prescription.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20other%20infections%2C%20resistance%20can%20develop%20if%20treatments%20aren%E2%80%99t%20given%20for%20long%20enough.%20This%20is%20particularly%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F11971765%2F%5C%22%3Ecase%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20tuberculosis%2C%20caused%20by%20a%20slow%20growing%20bacterium%20that%20requires%20a%20particularly%20long%20course%20of%20antibiotics%20to%20cure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20in%20humans%2C%20antibiotics%20are%20also%20used%20to%20prevent%20and%20treat%20infections%20in%20animals.%20However%2C%20a%20proportion%20of%20antibiotics%20are%20used%20for%20growth%20promotion.%20In%20Australia%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mja.com.au%2Fjournal%2F2019%2F211%2F4%2Fantibiotic-use-animals-and-humans-australia%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%2060%25%20of%20antibiotics%20were%20used%20in%20animals%20between%202005-2010%2C%20despite%20growth-promotion%20being%20phased%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20overuse%20a%20problem%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacteria%20become%20resistant%20to%20the%20effect%20of%20antibiotics%20through%20natural%20selection%20%E2%80%93%20those%20that%20survive%20exposure%20to%20antibiotics%20are%20the%20strains%20that%20have%20a%20mechanism%20to%20evade%20their%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20antibiotics%20are%20sometimes%20given%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flaninf%2Farticle%2FPIIS1473-3099(18)30279-2%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Eprevent%3C%2Fa%3E%20recurrent%20urinary%20tract%20infections%2C%20but%20a%20consequence%2C%20any%20infection%20that%20does%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fcid%2Farticle%2F73%2F3%2Fe782%2F6141409%5C%22%3Edevelop%3C%2Fa%3E%20tends%20to%20be%20with%20resistant%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20resistance%20to%20the%20commonly%20used%20first-line%20antibiotics%20occurs%2C%20we%20often%20need%20to%20reach%20deeper%20into%20the%20bag%20to%20find%20other%20effective%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20last-line%20antibiotics%20are%20those%20that%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4202707%2F%5C%22%3Esuperseded%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20had%20serious%20side%20effects%20or%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20given%20conveniently%20as%20tablets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20drugs%20for%20some%20bacteria%20have%20been%20developed%2C%20but%20many%20are%20much%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7955006%2F%5C%22%3Eexpensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20older%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreating%20antibiotics%20as%20a%20valuable%20resource%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20antibiotics%20as%20a%20valuable%20resource%20has%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F8856755%2F%5C%22%3Econcept%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%E2%80%9Cantimicrobial%20stewardship%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20programs%20to%20promote%20the%20responsible%20use%20of%20antibiotics.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20similar%20concept%20to%20environmental%20stewardship%20to%20prevent%20climate%20change%20and%20environmental%20degradation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotics%20are%20a%20rare%20class%20of%20medication%20where%20treatment%20of%20one%20patient%20can%20potentially%20affect%20the%20outcome%20of%20other%20patients%2C%20through%20the%20transmission%20of%20antibiotic%20resistant%20bacteria.%20Therefore%2C%20like%20efforts%20to%20combat%20climate%20change%2C%20antibiotic%20stewardship%20relies%20on%20changing%20individual%20actions%20to%20benefit%20the%20broader%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20climate%20change%2C%20antibiotic%20resistance%20is%20a%20complex%20problem%20when%20seen%20in%20a%20broader%20context.%20Studies%20have%20linked%20resistance%20to%20the%20values%20and%20priorities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flanplh%2Farticle%2FPIIS2542-5196(18)30186-4%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Eof%20governments%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20corruption%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20the%20availability%20of%20electricity%20and%20public%20services.%20This%20highlights%20that%20there%20are%20broader%20%E2%80%9Ccauses%20of%20the%20causes%E2%80%9D%2C%20such%20as%20public%20spending%20on%20sanitation%20and%20health%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fjac%2Farticle%2F74%2F9%2F2803%2F5512029%3Flogin%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Estudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20suggested%20individuals%20need%20to%20be%20considered%20within%20the%20broader%20social%20and%20institutional%20influences%20on%20prescribing%20behaviour.%20Like%20all%20human%20behaviour%2C%20antibiotic%20prescribing%20is%20complicated%2C%20and%20factors%20like%20what%20doctors%20feel%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnormal%E2%80%9D%20prescribing%2C%20whether%20junior%20staff%20feel%20they%20can%20challenge%20senior%20doctors%2C%20and%20even%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2016%2F10%2F07%2Fupshot%2Fyour-surgeon-is-probably-a-republican-your-psychiatrist-probably-a-democrat.html%5C%22%3Epolitical%20views%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20be%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20issues%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Finternational-journal-of-technology-assessment-in-health-care%2Farticle%2Fvalue-assessment-of-antimicrobials-and-the-implications-for-development-access-and-funding-of-effective-treatments-australian-stakeholder-perspective%2FD45758CFB95520DA4FF06E46135E0628%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20developing%20new%20antibiotics.%20When%20a%20new%20antibiotic%20is%20first%20approved%20for%20use%2C%20the%20first%20reaction%20for%20prescribers%20is%20not%20to%20use%20it%2C%20whether%20to%20ensure%20it%20retains%20its%20effectiveness%20or%20because%20it%20is%20often%20very%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20really%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fcid%2Farticle%2F50%2F8%2F1081%2F449089%3Flogin%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Eencourage%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20development%20of%20new%20antibiotics%2C%20particularly%20when%20pharma%20research%20and%20development%20budgets%20can%20easily%20be%20diverted%20to%20developing%20drugs%20for%20conditions%20patients%20take%20for%20years%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20slow%20moving%20pandemic%20of%20resistance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20fail%20to%20act%2C%20we%20are%20looking%20at%20an%20almost%20unthinkable%20scenario%20where%20antibiotics%20no%20longer%20work%20and%20we%20are%20cast%20back%20into%20the%20dark%20ages%20of%20medicine%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famr-review.org%2F%5C%22%3EDavid%20Cameron%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20former%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotic%20resistance%20is%20already%20a%20problem.%20Almost%20all%20infectious%20diseases%20physicians%20have%20had%20the%20dreaded%20call%20about%20patients%20with%20infections%20that%20were%20essentially%20untreatable%2C%20or%20where%20they%20had%20to%20scramble%20to%20find%20supplies%20of%20long-forgotten%20last-line%20antibiotics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20already%20hospitals%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20that%20have%20had%20to%20carefully%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reactgroup.org%2Fnews-and-views%2Fnews-and-opinions%2Fyear-2022%2Fthe-impact-of-antibiotic-resistance-on-cancer-treatment-especially-in-low-and-middle-income-countries-and-the-way-forward%2F%5C%22%3Econsider%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20viable%20to%20treat%20cancers%2C%20because%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6276316%2F%5C%22%3Ehigh%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20infections%20with%20antibiotic-resistant%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20global%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(21)02724-0%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20in%202019%2C%20almost%205%20million%20deaths%20occurred%20with%20an%20infection%20involving%20antibiotic-resistant%20bacteria.%20Some%201.3%20million%20would%20not%20have%20occurred%20if%20the%20bacteria%20were%20not%20resistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%E2%80%99s%202014%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famr-review.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FAMR%2520Review%2520Paper%2520-%2520Tackling%2520a%2520crisis%2520for%2520the%2520health%2520and%2520wealth%2520of%2520nations_1.pdf%5C%22%3EO%E2%80%99Neill%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20predicted%20deaths%20from%20antimicrobial%20resistance%20could%20rise%20to%2010%20million%20deaths%20each%20year%2C%20and%20cost%202-3.5%25%20of%20global%20GDP%2C%20by%202050%20based%20on%20trends%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20can%20we%20do%20about%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20lot%20we%20can%20do%20to%20prevent%20antibiotic%20resistance.%20We%20can%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marketingmag.com.au%2Fnews%2Ffilm-picking-gonorrhoea-wins-tropfest-prize%2F%5C%22%3Eraise%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs12889-019-7258-3%5C%22%3Eawareness%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20many%20infections%20will%20get%20better%20by%20themselves%2C%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20need%20antibiotics%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Euse%20the%20antibiotics%20we%20have%20more%20appropriately%20and%20for%20as%20short%20a%20time%20as%20possible%2C%20supported%20by%20co-ordinated%20clinical%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3437704%2F%5C%22%3Epublic%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amr.gov.au%2F%5C%22%3Enational%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flaninf%2Farticle%2FPIIS1473-3099(22)00796-4%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Eoversight%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.safetyandquality.gov.au%2Four-work%2Fantimicrobial-resistance%2Fantimicrobial-use-and-resistance-australia-surveillance-system%2Fabout-aura-surveillance-system%5C%22%3Emonitor%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20infections%20due%20to%20resistant%20bacterial%20to%20inform%20control%20policies%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Ereduce%20the%20inappropriate%20use%20of%20antibiotics%20in%20animals%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnam.edu%2Fantibiotic-resistance-in-humans-and-animals%2F%5C%22%3Egrowth%20promotion%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F11971765%2F%5C%22%3Ereduce%3C%2Fa%3E%20cross-transmission%20of%20resistant%20organisms%20in%20hospitals%20and%20in%20the%20community%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Eprevent%20infections%20by%20other%20means%2C%20such%20as%20clean%20water%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.who.int%2Firis%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F10665%2F204948%2FWHO_FWC_WSH_14.7_eng.pdf%5C%22%3Esanitation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hygiene%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fteams%2Fimmunization-vaccines-and-biologicals%2Fproduct-and-delivery-research%2Fanti-microbial-resistance%5C%22%3Evaccines%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Econtinue%20developing%20new%20antibiotics%20and%20alternatives%20to%20antibiotics%20and%20ensure%20the%20right%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flanepe%2Farticle%2FPIIS2666-7762(23)00124-2%2Ffulltext%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DWe%2520consider%2520four%2520incentive%2520options%2Cexclusivity%2520extensions%252C%2520and%2520milestone%2520payments.%5C%22%3Eincentives%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20in%20place%20to%20encourage%20a%20continuous%20pipeline%20of%20new%20drugs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAllen%20Cheng%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Infectious%20Diseases%2C%20Monash%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-rise-and-fall-of-antibiotics-what-would-a-post-antibiotic-world-look-like-213450%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699871450000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%