%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CBernie%E2%80%9D%20is%20clearly%20a%20very%20different%20figure%20to%20Harry%20Brown%20(he%20does%20nothing%20more%20controversial%20than%20letting%20down%20the%20tyres%20of%20antisocial%20cyclists).%20But%20as%20a%20film%20character%2C%20he%20nonetheless%20owes%20something%20to%20these%20cinematic%20counterparts.%20Like%20them%2C%20he%20carries%20the%20psychological%20scars%20of%20war%2C%20scars%20which%20wake%20him%20in%20the%20night%20and%20which%20take%20him%20back%20to%20the%20invasion%20beaches%20on%20the%20Normandy%20coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ED-Day%20on%20film%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Normandy%20invasion%20has%20been%20subject%20of%20various%20films%2C%20perhaps%20most%20famously%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0056197%2F%3Fref_%3Dfn_al_tt_1%5C%22%3EThe%20Longest%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1962).%20In%20the%20modern%20era%2C%20however%2C%20the%20D-Day%20film%20of%20most%20renown%20is%20undoubtedly%20Stephen%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0120815%2F%5C%22%3ESaving%20Private%20Ryan%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1998)%2C%20which%20starred%20Tom%20Hanks%20and%20Matt%20Damon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F9CiW_DgxCnQ%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntended%20as%20a%20homage%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FGreatest-Generation%5C%22%3Egreatest%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20film%20begins%20with%20an%20old%20soldier%20(the%20titular%20Private%20Ryan)%20searching%20the%20graves%20in%20the%20vast%20American%20military%20cemetery%20overlooking%20Omaha%20Beach%20in%20Normandy.%20This%20was%20the%20scene%20of%20some%20of%20the%20deadliest%20fighting%20on%20June%206%201944.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinding%20the%20grave%20he%20is%20looking%20for%2C%20the%20aged%20veteran%20drops%20to%20his%20knees%20before%20the%20camera%20zooms%20in%20on%20his%20eyes%20so%20that%20Spielberg%20can%20take%20us%20back%20to%20the%20battle%20on%20that%20grey%20spring%20morning.%20It%20is%20a%20powerful%20scene%2C%20and%20it%20has%20clearly%20inspired%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Escaper%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20director%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.co.uk%2Farticles%2Ftheres-a-lot-of-deep-deep-feeling-director-oliver-parker-on-his-new-film-the-great-escaper%5C%22%3EOliver%20Parker%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20shadow%20of%20%3Cem%3ESaving%20Private%20Ryan%3C%2Fem%3E%20looms%20large%20throughout.%20Like%20Spielberg%2C%20Parker%20takes%20us%20back%20to%20a%20Normandy%20burial%20ground%2C%20this%20time%20the%20Commonwealth%20War%20Graves%20Commission%20Cemetery%20in%20the%20town%20of%20Bayeux.%20He%20has%20us%20wander%20among%20the%20serried%20ranks%20of%20headstones%20and%2C%20via%20a%20series%20of%20flashbacks%2C%20we%20witness%20the%20carnage%20on%20the%20coast%20in%20washed-out%20colour%2C%20with%20the%20salt%20and%20sea%20spray%20in%20our%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20similarities%2C%20I%20think%2C%20reveal%20the%20ultimate%20point%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Escaper%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Through%20the%20familiar%20trope%20of%20a%20war-damaged%20British%20veteran%2C%20the%20film%20pays%20homage%20to%20those%20who%20fought%20and%20won%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20generation%20much%20vaunted%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20especially%20amid%20all%20the%20Brexit-induced%20forties%20nostalgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20Caine%E2%80%99s%20filmic%20finale%20also%20delivers%20an%20assertive%20British%20claim%20on%20the%20memory%20of%20D-Day%20(complete%20with%20obligatory%20digs%20at%20the%20%E2%80%9Clateness%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20conflict%20of%20the%20American%20ally).%20In%20effect%2C%20it%20is%20the%20cinematic%20counterpart%20to%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britishnormandymemorial.org%5C%22%3EBritish%20Normandy%20War%20Memorial%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20unveiled%20just%20two%20years%20ago%20in%20June%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20or%20not%20Parker%E2%80%99s%20film%20goes%20on%20to%20have%20the%20same%20cultural%20impact%20as%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20award-winning%20production%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20But%20thanks%20to%20the%20powerful%20presence%20of%20Michael%20Caine%20it%20surely%20stands%20a%20decent%20chance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESam%20Edwards%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20Reader%20in%20Modern%20Political%20History%2C%20Loughborough%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-great-escaper-michael-caines-final-film-is-britains-answer-to-saving-private-ryan-216315%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699777805000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09190441%2FScreenshot-2023-11-09-at-7.03.55%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fthe-great-escaper-michael-caine-final-film-review%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20film%2C%20which%20pays%20homage%20to%20the%20war%20generation%2C%20revels%20in%20forties%20nostalgia%20and%20stakes%20an%20assertive%20British%20claim%20to%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20Allied%20invasion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fthe-great-escaper-michael-caine-final-film-review%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Aware%20of%20States'%20Silencing%20of%20Dissenting%20Voices'%3A%20Academics%20Call%20on%20Turkey%20to%20Cut%20Ties%20With%20Israel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Close%20to%20300%20academics%20from%20Turkey%20have%20released%20a%20statement%20in%20support%20of%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20under%20attack%20from%20Israel.%20The%20statement%20highlights%20how%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20attacks%20on%20October%207%20is%20now%20a%20pretext%20for%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20massacre%20of%20Palestinian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECalling%20themselves%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FAcademics_for_Peace%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%98Academics%20for%20Peace%20from%20Turkey%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98%2C%20the%20group%20has%20called%20on%20Turkey%20to%20severe%20all%20military%2C%20commercial%20and%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20signatories%20noted%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20actions%20amount%20to%20%E2%80%9Cethnic%20cleansing%20and%20even%20genocide.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20the%20statement%20in%20full%20and%20its%20signatories%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20which%20has%20been%20illegally%20occupying%20the%20Palestinian%20territories%20for%2056%20years%20and%20has%20been%20besieging%20Gaza%20since%202006%20in%20violation%20of%20international%20law%2C%20as%20also%20stated%20by%20the%20Secretary-General%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20is%20today%20committing%20another%20crime%20against%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20in%20front%20of%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20whole%20world.%20On%20October%207%2C%202023%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9CJoint%20Room%20for%20Palestinian%20Resistance%20Factions%E2%80%9D%20consisting%20of%20a%20total%20of%2012%20Palestinian%20organisations%20with%20diverse%20political%20orientations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20often%20reported%20in%20the%20media%20only%20as%20Hamas%20%E2%80%93%20crossed%20the%20Gaza%20border%20and%20killed%20more%20than%201400%20people%2C%20most%20of%20them%20civilians%2C%20with%20air%20and%20ground%20attacks.%C2%A0%20The%20Israeli%20state%20thereupon%2C%20using%20this%20massacre%20almost%20as%20an%20excuse%20or%20even%20%E2%80%9Copportunity%E2%80%9D%2C%20began%20to%20apply%20the%20heaviest%20state%20terror%20against%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20to%20date.%20In%20the%20midst%20of%20these%20massacres%2C%20we%20witnessed%20the%20constant%20bombing%20of%20hospitals%2C%20the%20complete%20destruction%20of%20two%20hospitals%2C%20the%20bombing%20of%20ambulance%20convoys%20and%20the%20open%20declaration%20of%20the%20Israeli%20state%20that%20it%20will%20not%20recognise%20any%20law%20of%20war.%20As%20of%20November%206%2C%20the%20death%20toll%20in%20Gaza%20is%20estimated%20to%20have%20exceeded%2010%2C000%2C%20including%20thousands%20of%20children%20and%20women.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Israeli%20government%20today%20uses%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20recent%20attacks%20as%20a%20pretext%20for%20its%20massacres%2C%20but%20we%20know%20that%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%20intense%20repression%20and%20violence%20by%20the%20Israeli%20security%20forces%20even%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20Hamas.%20The%20Israeli%20government%2C%20which%20has%20been%20labelled%20an%20apartheid%20regime%20by%20many%20Jewish%20diaspora%20initiatives%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20well%20as%20by%20political%20and%20civil%20initiatives%20of%20Israeli%20citizens%2C%20implies%20in%20front%20of%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20world%20that%20it%20aims%20to%20wipe%20out%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%2C%20estimated%20at%202.2%20million%2C%20from%20the%20face%20of%20the%20earth.%C2%A0%20The%20land%20operation%20launched%20by%2